<article>
    <h1>EL&#xAD;E&#xAD;VATED NORTH IN&#xAD;DIAN STREET FOOD</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200724/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-07-24"><time>2020-07-24</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | HAPPENINGS</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>North In­dian restau­rant Shahi Ma­ha­rani’s Royal Feast ($25+, above) comes in the form of a bento that is avail­able for de­liv­ery or take­away only.</p>
    <p>The Chicken Makhan­wala (But­ter Chicken) has an aro­matic smok­i­ness. The chicken is first mar­i­nated overnight, then fur­ther mar­i­nated in a mix that in­cludes yo­gurt and garam masala, be­fore it is grilled in the tan­door. The restau­rant grinds its own garam masala from whole spices such as nut­meg, cloves and cin­na­mon sticks.</p>
    <p>The crust of the mini veg­etable samosas re­mains crispy even as they cool down.</p>
    <p>The bento comes with a choice of bread. I rec­om­mend the Gar­lic Naan.</p>
    <p>For the bento, there is no min­i­mum or­der for de­liv­ery ($8+) within the Cen­tral Busi­ness Dis­trict.</p>
    <p>Last month, the restau­rant also launched new street food items that are avail­able for dine-in, take­away or de­liv­ery only on week­ends.</p>
    <p>The Keema Pav ($18++ for dine-in, $16+ for take­away or de­liv­ery) is spiced minced mut­ton served with toasted buns with onion and lime on the side. The Vada Pav ($18++ for dine-in, $16+ for take­away or de­liv­ery) is a deep-fried potato dumpling in a bun with a house-made spicy-sweet and tangy tamarind sauce.</p>
    <p>An ap­petis­ing dish is the Aloo Tikki Chole Chaat ($18++ for dine-in and $18+ for take­away or de­liv­ery), which com­prises potato cut­lets topped with spiced chick­peas, finely diced onions, pome­gran­ate seeds and crispy chick­pea ver­mi­celli. The dress­ing of whipped yo­gurt, mint chut­ney and sweet-sour tamarind sauce is a bal­ance of sweet, spicy and sour.</p>
    <p>For a meat-free biryani that is just as hearty and tasty, go for the Dum</p>
    <p>Jack­fruit Biryani</p>
    <p>($26++ for dine-in,</p>
    <p>$26+ for take­away or de­liv­ery, right).</p>
    <p>The jack­fruit cooked in masala has a sur­pris­ing meat-like tex­ture and is steeped in flavour.</p>
    <p>No food colour­ing is used in the prepa­ra­tion of the bas­mati rice, to which saf­fron and turmeric are added.</p>
    <p>For the non-bento items, de­liv­ery is avail­able with a min­i­mum or­der of $40. De­liv­ery charges de­pend on lo­ca­tion.</p>
    <p>WHERE: Shahi Ma­ha­rani, 03-21B Raf­fles City Shop­ping Cen­tre, 252 North Bridge Road</p>
    <p>MRT: City Hall</p>
    <p>OPEN: Noon to 2.30pm daily; 6.30 to 9.30pm (Sun­days to Thurs­days); 6.30 to 10.30pm (Fri­days and Satur­days) TEL: 6235-8840</p>
    <p>INFO: E-mail en­quiries@shahima­ha­rani.com or go to shahima­ha­rani.com. To or­der, What­sApp 8564-7012 or call 6235-8840. De­liv­ery is also avail­able via Food­panda and GrabFood.</p>

